foreTrapLogModule.name: foreTrapLogModule
foreTrapLogModule.contactinfo: Postal: FORE Systems Inc. 1000 FORE Drive Warrendale, PA 15086-7502 Tel: +1 724 742 6900 Email: nm_mibs@fore.com Web: http://www.fore.com
foreTrapLogModule.description: This MIB module defines the FORE Systems specific Log information for Traps. It provides for a Log table, Var table and Threshold table. Each Log table entry contains general information on the traps that occured, number of times and the last time they occured. The Var table contains information on the trap variables reported with specific traps. The Threshold table is a fully populated table which has the thresholds & timeperiods defined for all the traps.

trapLogTable.name: trapLogTable
trapLogTable.description: A table consisting of entries with trap information

trapLogEntry.name: trapLogEntry
trapLogEntry.description: A table entry containing a trap number, and some information on the trap.

trapLogIndex.name: trapLogIndex
trapLogIndex.description: The sequence number of this trap occurence. This entry uniquely identifies an entry in the trapLogTable

trapLogEnterprise.name: trapLogEnterprise
trapLogEnterprise.description: The enterprise oid of this trap. This used with the trapLogGenericId and trapLogId uniquely identifies the trap type which occured.

trapLogGenericId.name: trapLogGenericId
trapLogGenericId.description: The value of this object identifies the generic trap type that occured.

trapLogId.name: trapLogId
trapLogId.description: The value of this object identifies the specific trap type that occured.

trapLogXmits.name: trapLogXmits
trapLogXmits.description: The number of times this trap was transmitted out on the network to trap destinations.

trapLogLastXmit.name: trapLogLastXmit
trapLogLastXmit.description: The sysUptime at which this trap was last transmitted to trap destinations.

trapLogEvents.name: trapLogEvents
trapLogEvents.description: The number of times this trap event occured.

trapLogLastEvent.name: trapLogLastEvent
trapLogLastEvent.description: The sysUptime at which this trap event last occured.

trapLogVarTable.name: trapLogVarTable
trapLogVarTable.description: A table of trap variables corresponding to trap occurences.

trapLogVarEntry.name: trapLogVarEntry
trapLogVarEntry.description: A table entry containing informaiton about a trap variable reported for one of the trap occurences.

trapLogVarIndex.name: trapLogVarIndex
trapLogVarIndex.description: The Variable index. This number identifies the index of this variable in a list of variables reported with one trap occurence. The list of variables are in the order of the variables given in the TRAP definition for this trap.

trapLogVarOID.name: trapLogVarOID
trapLogVarOID.description: This is the OID of the trap variable.

trapLogVarValue.name: trapLogVarValue
trapLogVarValue.description: This is the value of the trap variable.

trapThresholdTable.name: trapThresholdTable
trapThresholdTable.description: A table of thresholds and time periods for the switch traps, which determine when a trap is transmitted to the trap destinations

trapThresholdEntry.name: trapThresholdEntry
trapThresholdEntry.description: A table entry containing the trap type and the threshold value and the time period for the trap.

trapThresholdTrapEnterprise.name: trapThresholdTrapEnterprise
trapThresholdTrapEnterprise.description: The enterprise OID of this trap.

trapThresholdValue.name: trapThresholdValue
trapThresholdValue.description: The value of the threshold for the number of trap occurences after which the trap gets sent to the destinations.

trapThresholdTimePeriod.name: trapThresholdTimePeriod
trapThresholdTimePeriod.description: This value has to be used in conjuntion with the trapThresholdValue. It gives the time period over which the threshold is valid. i.e if trapThresholdValue trap events occur, Or if the time since the last transmission is greater than this object's value, the trap gets transmitted out.

trapThresholdTableReset.name: trapThresholdTableReset
trapThresholdTableReset.description: When user sets this object to enable(1), all the threshold table values are reset to default values. The value of this object would be disable(2), after the reconfiguration.
